    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-04-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="120" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <head>No. 120.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-04-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 3,
                            1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Mr. Lowell states that Walsh has been already released, and that so have
                        Hart and O’Connor. No Joseph Dalton has been arrested. White has been
                        released on parole.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
